      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "This accepted answer is correct in suggesting <code>contains()</code>, but it has it backwards with using <code>toLowerCase()</code>. Ideally a locale-aware uppercase function should be used; if not possible or not desired, then <b>toUpperCase()</b> is preferable for normalizing strings. See <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/14128850/3665087\">stackoverflow.com/a/14128850/3665087</a>"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
